race.comment: ANDREW'S MEMORY (4) continues to race well and rates a leading player. Ran on hard to score two back then did the same to run into the placings latest. Drawn for a good run. BROWN NOSE DAY GAL (11) has been gritty winning her last two starts and has to go in. Keeps improving and keeps finding to score. This tougher but hard to knock the recent form. SEE YA LATER BABY (8) wasn't far away last time and with the claim will give a sight again. KATIM'S CLUB (13) was safely held last time but trip suits and best figures stack up. Could be over the odds. THE BACK PAGE (9) next elect. Really caught the eye late last start at Strathalbyn.
